                    "CAs validate identity and issue digitally signed certificates binding identity to keys.", DifficultyLevel.BEGINNER),
                QuizQuestion("cq9", "Which hash function is considered broken for collision resistance?",
                    ["SHA-256", "SHA-3", "SHA-1", "BLAKE2"], 2,
                    "SHA-1 collision attacks are practical (SHAttered, 2017); deprecated for security.", DifficultyLevel.INTERMEDIATE),
                QuizQuestion("cq10", "What is a nonce in cryptographic context?",
                    ["A number used only once", "A secret key", "A type of cipher", "A hash output"], 0,
